headline: AbbVie raises full-year forecast, Newell Brands stock plunges

Stay up to date on the latest market action, minute-by-minute, with Yahoo Finance's Market Minute.

headline: AbbVie Beats Third-Quarter Estimates. There’s More to the Drugmaker’s Earnings.
summary: AbbVie  stock dropped Friday after the biopharmaceutical company reported mixed results across its drug portfolios in the third quarter.  Shares declined 4.7% to $217.50, putting AbbVie on pace for its lowest same-day percentage decrease since May 14, according to Dow Jones Market Data.  Pharma peers traded mixed: Johnson & Johnson fell slightly while Pfizer gained 0.7%.
